section.section:
The ordinance adopted by the Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City may not restrict:
The placement of signs, including advertisements:
Inside licensed premises;
On commercial vehicles used for transporting alcoholic beverages; or
In conjunction with a 1-day alcoholic beverages license or a temporary license granted by the Board of License Commissioners;
Any sign that contains the name or slogan of the licensed premises that has been placed for the purpose of identifying the licensed premises;
Except for billboards and freestanding signboards, any sign for which zoning board approval or a minor privilege permit is required;
Any sign that contains a generic description of beer, wine, liquor, or spirits, or any other generic description of alcoholic beverages;
Any neon or electrically charged sign on licensed premises that is provided as part of a promotion of a particular brand of alcoholic beverage;
Any sign on an MTA vehicle or a taxicab;
Any sign on property owned, leased, or operated by the Maryland Stadium Authority;
Any sign at Memorial Stadium;
Any sign at a facility that operates in accordance with a license issued under § 11-304 of the Business Regulation Article; or
Any sign on property adjacent to an interstate highway.
